#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:1
msgid "Operaton Deployment (VM)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:3
msgid ""
"Operaton is the BPMN/DMN execution engine. It runs as a single Docker "
"container on the VM, shared between ACC and PROD (process definition version "
"tags differentiate environments). It is exposed via Caddy at `https://"
"operaton.open-regels.nl`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:7
msgid "Repository structure"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:9
msgid ""
"Operaton deployment is managed directly on the VM. There is no Operaton-"
"specific folder in the `ronl-business-api` repository — Operaton's Docker "
"image and configuration are maintained separately from the application code."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:13
msgid "Starting Operaton"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:15
msgid ""
"ssh user@open-regels.nl\n"
"\n"
"# Create the Operaton directory\n"
"mkdir -p ~/operaton\n"
"cd ~/operaton\n"
"\n"
"# Create docker-compose.yml\n"
"cat > docker-compose.yml << 'EOF'\n"
"version: '3.8'\n"
"services:\n"
"  operaton:\n"
"    image: operaton/operaton:latest\n"
"    container_name: operaton\n"
"    ports:\n"
"      - \"127.0.0.1:8090:8080\"\n"
"    environment:\n"
"      - DB_DRIVER=org.h2.Driver\n"
"      - DB_URL=jdbc:h2:./camunda-h2-databases/process-"
"engine;TRACE_LEVEL_FILE=0;DB_CLOSE_ON_EXIT=FALSE\n"
"      - DB_USERNAME=sa\n"
"      - DB_PASSWORD=\n"
"    volumes:\n"
"      - operaton-data:/camunda\n"
"    restart: always\n"
"    networks:\n"
"      - npm-network\n"
"\n"
"volumes:\n"
"  operaton-data:\n"
"\n"
"networks:\n"
"  npm-network:\n"
"    external: true\n"
"EOF\n"
"\n"
"docker compose up -d"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:55
msgid "Verify"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:57
msgid ""
"curl https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest/engine\n"
"# Expected: [{\"name\":\"default\"}]"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:62
msgid ""
"The Operaton Cockpit UI is available at `https://operaton.open-regels.nl/app/"
"cockpit/`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:66
msgid "Deploying BPMN/DMN process definitions"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:68
msgid ""
"Process definitions (`.bpmn` and `.dmn` files) are deployed to Operaton via "
"its REST API. RONL ships with a `zorgtoeslag` process:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:70
msgid ""
"# Deploy zorgtoeslag BPMN\n"
"curl -X POST https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest/deployment/create \\"
"\n"
"  -F \"deployment-name=zorgtoeslag\" \\\n"
"  -F \"deploy-changed-only=true\" \\\n"
"  -F \"zorgtoeslag.bpmn=@processes/zorgtoeslag.bpmn\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:80
msgid "Integration with the Business API"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:82
msgid "The backend connects to Operaton via `OPERATON_BASE_URL`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:84
msgid ""
"OPERATON_BASE_URL=https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest\n"
"OPERATON_TIMEOUT=30000"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:89
msgid ""
"`packages/backend/src/services/operaton.service.ts` handles all Operaton API "
"calls. The service injects user context variables and maps Operaton "
"responses to the Business API response format."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:93
msgid "Updating Operaton"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:95
msgid ""
"cd ~/operaton\n"
"docker compose pull\n"
"docker compose up -d\n"
"docker compose logs -f operaton    # verify startup"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/ronl-business-api%5Cdeveloper%5Cdeployment%5Coperaton.md:102
msgid ""
"Check the Operaton release notes before upgrading — BPMN/DMN deployment "
"compatibility should be verified in the ACC environment first."
msgstr ""
